# Local dev tests for OBOFunction — agent-chat endpoint
#
# Requires: REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
#
# The proxy exposes ONLY POST /api/agent/chat (plus /liveness, /readiness). It validates the
# inbound user JWT (aud api://<proxy-app>), resolves the signed-in user's profile via OBO
# (SharePoint UPS + Graph) on the first turn, injects it as context, and calls the Foundry
# hosted agent as the user. The agent answers and runs its local search_faq tool.
#
# Token strategy: shell out to `az account get-access-token`. Never commit a real token.
#   az account get-access-token --resource api://<proxy-app-client-id> --query accessToken -o tsv | Set-Clipboard
#
# Alternative: set an env var and use {{$processEnv OBO_TOKEN}} (launch `code .` from the same shell):
#   $env:OBO_TOKEN = az account get-access-token --resource api://<proxy-app-client-id> --query accessToken -o tsv

@functionUrl = http://localhost:7071

# Paste a freshly minted token here when testing (Bearer prefix added below). DO NOT COMMIT IT.
@token = PASTE_PROXY_USER_TOKEN_HERE

### Liveness
GET {{functionUrl}}/liveness

### Ask the agent — using the pasted @token above
POST {{functionUrl}}/api/agent/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Who am I and what are my interests?",
  "previousResponseId": null
}

### Ask the agent — using the OBO_TOKEN env var (launch `code .` from the same shell)
POST {{functionUrl}}/api/agent/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{$processEnv OBO_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "List my profile.",
  "previousResponseId": null
}
